es  , which is traditionallypronounced ‘mingiz’."]},{"name":"Manners","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Mesnières-en-Bray in Seine-Maritime, recorded in the 13th century as <i>Maneria</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>manere</i> ‘to remain, abide, reside’. See also   Menzies  ."]},{"name":"Menzie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Menzies  ."]},{"name":"McMinn","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Méinn</b> ‘son of <i>Méinn</i>’, a Gaelic interpretation of   Menzies   as a relationship surname."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs John Menzies was born about 1325, in Weem, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with John De Menzies 4th Menzies Clan Chief."},"et":{"about 1325–":"umbes 1325–Surnud","1323–1410":"1323–1410","1353–1411":"1353–1411","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1325":"1325","1411":"1411","1323":"1323","1410":"1410","about 1325":"umbes 1325","1353":"1353","Weem, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Weem, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Castle Menzies, Weem, Aberfeldy, Perth, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Weem, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1325–":"noin 1325–Kuollut","1323–1410":"1323–1410","1353–1411":"1353–1411","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1411":"1411","1323":"1323","1410":"1410","about 1325":"noin 1325","1353":"1353","Weem, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Weem, Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Castle Menzies, Weem, Aberfeldy, Perth, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Weem, Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1325–":"environ 1325–Décédée","1323–1410":"1323–1410","1353–1411":"1353–1411","1325–Female":"1325–Décédée","1325":"1325","1411":"1411","1323":"1323","1410":"1410","about 1325":"environ 1325","1353":"1353","Weem, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Weem, Per